FT  26 MAY 94 / World Trade News: WTO 'will miss start date'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
France said yesterday the Gatt world trade body's offspring, the World Trade
Organisation would fail to meet its start-up goal of next January 1, and
threw its weight behind Geneva's bid to host the WTO, Reuter reports from
Paris.
'We will not meet the start-up date of January 1, 1995, for the very simple
reason that we want to wait for ratification by the US Congress and then,
naturally, by the French parliament,' industry and trade minister Gerard
Longuet said. Answering a question in the National Assembly (lower house),
Mr Longuet said history proved 'it is better for an international
organisation to be sure the Americans will ratify (it) before we ratify it
so as not to be caught in an uncertain position.'
