<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Cementone shares fall on warning
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JEAN MARSHALL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Cementone fell 16p to 80p yesterday as Mr Alan Clements, chairman,
told the annual meeting that first half profits would be 'materially lower
than market expectations'.
The specialist paints and building chemicals maker came to the market in
January via a reverse takeover of Multitrust, the property investment
company. Its shares, which were placed at 73p, began trading ahead of
expectations at 87p.
Mr Clements said that intense margin pressure from competitors in
conjunction with promotional activities in both the paints and chemicals
market sectors had resulted in a continuing squeeze on margins.
Management had taken action, he said, which had already resulted in margin
and profitability improvements.
He was confident that normal levels of profitability would be restored in
the second half. For the year to December 31 1993 pre-tax profits were
Pounds 1.21m (Pounds 995,046).
</TEXT>
