<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAY 94 / London Stock Exchange: Inflation worries hit M&amp;S
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, CHRISTOPHER PRICE and JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Disappointing headline results from Marks and Spencer, together with a
cautious statement, saw the shares fall in busy turnover of 8.5m yesterday.
Profits of Pounds 851.5m compared with forecasts of Pounds 865m contained a
surprise increase in the pension contribution. Otherwise analysts declared
themselves fairly satisfied with the underlying performance.
But the shares closed 12 1/2 off at 412p as some investors took their cue
from Marks' remarks that cost price inflation is returning to the retail
market. 'Some institutions think they might have a racier ride in some of
the more undervalued and risky stores stocks,' said one dealer. Analysts
kept their 1995 forecasts in the Pounds 940m to Pounds 960m range, although
a number did lower their performance rating in the light of the company
statement.
