<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAY 94 / World Commodities Prices: Cocoa hits 6 1/4 -year highs -
Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
London COCOA futures surged to 6 1/4 -year highs yesterday as investment
fund buying swamped the market, leaving many in the trade wrong-footed.
The July contract closed at Pounds 1,066 a tonne, up Pounds 68, after
touching Pounds 1,085 at one stage. 'It looks very, very good. It's a got a
strong base and the upside potential is a couple of hundred pounds,' one
trader said.
At the London Metal Exchange three months COPPER hit a 16-month peak of
Dollars 2,335 a tonne in the morning, underpinned by speculative buying,
fund interest and short-covering. But profit-taking set in and the price was
trimmed to Dollars 2,296.50, up Dollars 19.50 on balance. Most other LME
contracts lost early gains.
