<TEXT>
Sir, I note that Michael Thompson-Noel 'hurled himself out of London down
the motorway to Solsbury Hill very close to Bath' to support the protest
against the proposed by-pass (Hawks &amp; Handsaws, May 21/22).
Surely those who are concerned about road building 'madness' should set an
example by leaving their cars at home whenever possible. Why did he not use
public transport from London to Bath - and then proceed the short distance
from Bath by road?
Ivor Broom,
Cherry Lawn, Bridle Lane,
