<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAY 94 / Competitiveness - The White Paper: EU funding competition
launched
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A new competition for projects to bid for European Union economic
regeneration funds, called Regional Challenge, is to follow City Challenge
and Rural Challenge, which were designed to help urban and rural areas in
economic difficulty.
Regional Challenge is related to money from the European Regional
Development Fund, set up to help the EU's less prosperous areas. The
government is promising prize money of Pounds 150m-Pounds 200m to an
unspecified number of schemes, put together by local public-private-sector
partnerships, in the first round of the competition. More competitions are
to be held three years later.
