<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAY 94 / Competitiveness - The White Paper: Help and advice centres
for small businesses to grow
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government is to extend the role played by Business Links, the advice
and help centres for smaller companies which Mr Michael Heseltine has
championed.
The measures for England could speed the pace at which Chambers of Commerce,
Training and Enterprise Councils, Enterprise Agencies and the Department of
Trade and Industry form the Business Link partnerships.
There are 22 Business Links; the DTI expects 50 to be in place by the end of
the year, and full coverage for England by the end of 1995. Yesterday extra
funding for TECs that have already set up Business Links or are making
progress in that direction was promised.
The level of export support for small businesses is also extended, placing
about 70 new export advisers in Business Link offices throughout the
country.
