<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: America leads the way
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
America led the way last week, the only sizeable impetus as the FT-Actuaries
World Index rose by 1.05 per cent.
US stocks climbed on the tightening of US monetary policy. Canada followed
its neighbour, but its equity market got an additional boost from its base
metal content.
Mexico, depressed this year, and extremely sensitive to interest rate
action, gained most. In part, this was a pragmatic response to the
performance of the ruling party's presidential candidate, Mr Ernesto
Zedillo, in an earlier, televised debate.
